org.knime.core.data.container

Class AbstractCellFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.data.container.AbstractCellFactory
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CellFactory
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    RegressionPredictorCellFactory, RoundDoubleCellFactory, SingleCellFactory

    public abstract class AbstractCellFactory
extends Object
implements CellFactory
    Default implementation of a CellFactory, which creates more than a single new column.

    As of v2.5 the input table can be processed concurrently. This property should only be set if (i) the processing of an individual row is expensive, i.e. takes significantly longer than pure I/O and (ii) there are no interdependency between the row calculations.

    Author:
    Bernd Wiswedel, University of Konstanz
    See Also:
    SingleCellFactory

      • setParallelProcessing

        public final void setParallelProcessing(boolean value)
        Enables or disables parallel processing of the rows. The two relevant parameters for the number of parallel workers and maximum work queue size are determined automatically based on the number of available cores.
        Parameters:
        value - If to enable parallel processing (assumes independency of individual row calculations).
        Since:
        2.5

      • isParallelProcessing

        public final boolean isParallelProcessing()
        Returns true if parallel processing is enabled, either via the constructor argument or by calling the setParallelProcessing(boolean) method.
        Returns:
        true if input is processed concurrently. If true, the values for getMaxParallelWorkers() and getMaxQueueSize() will be at least 1 (whereby 1 is a corner case where the input is processed synchronously with one dedicated worker thread).
        Since:
        2.5.2

      • setParallelProcessing

        public final void setParallelProcessing(boolean value,
                                        int maxParallelWorkers,
                                        int maxQueueSize)
        Enables or disables parallel processing of the rows. The two relevant parameters for the number of parallel workers and maximum work queue need to be specified.
        Parameters:
        value - If to enable parallel processing (assumes independence of individual row calculation).
        maxParallelWorkers - The number of parallel execution threads to process the rows. This value may be overruled by the global thread pool limit.
        maxQueueSize - The number of finished calculations that are stored in memory before further executions are paused. (Background: The rows are processed in the order defined by the input table's iterator. If a certain row computation takes long the framework needs to temporarily cache the results of the following rows - the cache size is determined by this parameter. If this cache is full, no further row computations are queued until the long-running task finishes.)
        Since:
        2.5

      • getMaxParallelWorkers

        public final int getMaxParallelWorkers()
        The number of parallel workers or -1 if the input is processed sequentially. See setParallelProcessing(boolean, int, int) for a detailed description. If parallel processing is enabled but no detailed parameters are provided, the number of workers and the queue size are determined heuristically based on the available processors.
        Returns:
        The number of parallel workers or -1.
        Since:
        2.5.2

      • getMaxQueueSize

        public final int getMaxQueueSize()
        The size of the processing queue if parallel processing is enabled or -1 if the input is processed sequentially. See setParallelProcessing(boolean, int, int) and getMaxParallelWorkers() for details.
        Returns:
        the maxQueueSize or -1.
        Since:
        2.5.2

      • getColumnSpecs

        public DataColumnSpec[] getColumnSpecs()
        The column specs for the cells that are generated in the getCells() method. This method is only called once, there is no need to cache the return value. The length of the returned array must match the length of the array returned by the getCells(DataRow) method and also the types must match, i.e. the type of the respective DataColumnSpec must be of the same type or a super type of the cell as returned by getCells(DataRow).
        Specified by:
        getColumnSpecs in interface CellFactory
        Returns:
        The specs to the newly created cells.

      • setProgress

        @Deprecated
public void setProgress(int curRowNr,
                                    int rowCount,
                                    RowKey lastKey,
                                    ExecutionMonitor exec)
        Deprecated. use setProgress(long, long, RowKey, ExecutionMonitor) instead which supports more than Integer.MAX_VALUE rows
        This method is called when a row has been processed. It allows the implementor to set progress in the execution monitor and also some meaningful progress message.

        Note, you don't need to check exec.checkCanceled() in the implementation as this is done in the calling class.

        Specified by:
        setProgress in interface CellFactory
        Parameters:
        curRowNr - The number of the row just processed
        rowCount - The total number of rows.
        lastKey - The row's key.
        exec - The execution monitor to report progress to.
